Detect Sentiment Transformation: Determine the Sentiment of Text

In CRM Analytics, text fields show valuable information such as product reviews and social media posts. Use the Detect Sentiment transformation in a Data Prep recipe to quickly categorize text into sentiments.

REQUIRED USER PERMISSIONS
USER PERMISSIONS
NEEDED
To create a recipe: Edit CRM Analytics Dataflows OR Edit Dataset Recipes

This transformation works on a text (dimension) column and supports English text only. It processes non-English text as English and ignores images, including emoji. If the input value is null or an empty string (''), the transformation assigns the sentiment as Neutral or with a value of 2.5.

In a Transform node of a Data Prep recipe, select the text (dimension) column that contains the text for sentiment analysis in the Preview tab.
In the Transform toolbar, click the Detect Sentiment button.
Optionally, use More Options to change the output type or to show sentiment scores.

When determining sentiment, Detect Sentiment classifies the text into groups from 1 through 5.

The sentiment values are mapped as follows:

Positive is >3.50 and <= 5.00
Neutral is >= 2.50 and < 3.5
Negative is >= 1.00 and < 2.50

Einstein self-assesses its confidence in the accuracy of each sentiment option. Sentiment scores are decimal values that add up to 1 and can be used in formulas.

Detect Sentiment Model Card
In CRM Analytics, the Detect Sentiment transformation uses the model to determine whether the sentiment of text is positive, negative, or neutral. Use this model card to better understand the model, how itâ€™s trained, its capabilities, its intended use, and its limitations.
